    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2009-07-16" ;
    bibo:startPage "29" ;
    bibo:volume "2160" ;
    dc:creator "Kjaerandsen, Jostein; Martinsson, Svante; Hedmark, Kjell; Evenhuis, Neal L." ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "On the genus Urytalpa Edwards (Diptera: Keroplatidae) in the Nordic and Nearctic regions, with fixation of a new type species and a key to world males" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319516> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319516>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Type material studied. — A. Type series of Platyura ochracea Meigen, 1818 at the MNHN collections in Paris. 1 = male with cleared abdomen in glycerine in separate microvial. This specimen is in best agreement with the original description and selected as the lectotype for Orfelia ochracea (Meigen, 1818) comb. n. = Orfelia unicolor (Staeger, 1840) syn. n. 2 = Orfelia sp. lacking abdomen. 3 = female Neoplatyura cf. flava (Macquart, 1826). — B. Male holotype of Urytalpa dorsalis (Staeger, 1840) sp. restit. from the ZMUC collections in Copenhagen. This specimen in near perfect condition (only lacking right mid leg beyond trochanter) is designated as the new type species for Urytalpa due to original misidentification of Platyura ochracea Meigen, 1818 by Edwards (1924, 1929)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5319516/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

